---
title: One-Pan Shrimp Lo Mein with Udon Noodles, Green Beans, and Carrots
description: Udon noodles lend themselves naturally to stir-frys. Because they’re thick and chewy, they do a great job of soaking up the sauce (here, that’s a mix of hoisin and soy). All that’s needed to make a recipe like this complete is a mix of veggies and a hearty protein; we’re providing you with crisp green beans, crunchy carrot, and perfectly plump shrimp.
